A fire has broken out at the police flats in Sophiatown in Johannesburg. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - A fire broke out at the police flats in Sophiatown on Saturday afternoon.
Initial reports say the fire started on the 8th floor and is spreading to the roof. READ: Unions plead for safe working conditions in government buildings According to locals, the building in Millar street has not been effectively maintained for a number of years. READ: Another government building declared unsafe Residents have complained that the building has a problem with water access, including inoperable fire hoses. Other issues include lack of refuse removal and broken windows.